(DS2 would be the king!) Years ago I made up a piece of SAS code to demonstrate the basic idea of Map-Reduce. Now this idea can be best implemented by this piece of workable program with PROC DS2 (tested in SAS 9.4 TS1M2, Win7):
 PROC DS2;
/* create some data &#8211;/ data input_data / overwrite = yes; dcl double d; method init(); &#160;&#160; dcl int i; &#160;&#160; do i = 1 to 10000000; &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; /&#8211; create some money values &#8211;*/ &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; d = round( (ranuni(123) * 10 ), .

1. Permutation and Combination  data null;
n = 5;
r = 2;
*the factorial of a number;
fact=fact(n);
*for positive integers, fact(n) = gamma(n+1);
gamm=gamma(n + 1);
*C(n,r): number of combinations of n objects selected r ;
*n! / [r!(n-r)!];
comb1 = comb(n,r);
comb2 = fact(n) / (fact&reg; * fact(n-r));
comb3 = gamma(n+1) / (gamma(r+1) * gamma(n-r+1));
comb4 = exp(lcomb(n,r));
comb5 = exp(lgamma(n+1)-lgamma(r+1)-lgamma(n-r+1));
*A(n,r): number of permutation (ordered arrangements);

