 3. Step 1 of 6: Create a new study (create_new_study.sas) Open create_new_study.sas in C:Program FilesCDISC Expressprograms, you can see only one line of a macro call:
 %addnewstudy(studyname=my new study);
 Just assign a study name to the macro variable, &amp;studyname, e.g, “CLINCAP”:
 %addnewstudy(studyname= CLINCAP);
 Submit the codes, you can find a folder named “CLINCAP” with the same structure as the two demo studies imbedded in this application(example1 and example2) in C:Program FilesCDISC Expressstudies, see(the left and right panels are folders and files before and after the execution of create_new_study.

